        <div class="body">
            <p>bootstrap() was designed to be a fluent interface because the intention is that it is setting the application/bootstrap state. Additionally, the fact that it can take multiple signatures -- including <em>no</em> arguments -- makes having a standard return value a more sane API.</p>

<p>Marking as "won't fix".</p>

